Given duplicate `(Work, Material)` combinations in the data table (e.g. Work 2 + Material 1 appears twice with different category columns populated), a simple `INDEX/MATCH` on row alone could return the wrong row. A robust LibreOffice-compatible approach is to use `SUMPRODUCT` and choose the correct category column based on the report rowâ€™s Category Type. That will return the correct value and safely handle duplicates by summing the one matching nonzero category value.

Next Iâ€™ll write formulas into `D17:D22`, save to the output directory with the same filename, recalculate, reload, verify values, and ensure the sheet name remains `Sheet1`.
